Note: P2-D Q3 FFI Foundation Smoke Test — Objective-C Convention (Darwin)
Note:
Note: Per CEO Q3 amendment 2026-05-24, the objc convention must ship as a
Note: fully implemented end-to-end FFI path. This file declares an
Note: objc-convention External and exercises it; on Darwin targets the
Note: codegen must emit `callq _objc_msgSend@PLT` instead of the literal
Note: method name; on non-Darwin targets the linker must reject with a
Note: clean diagnostic.
Note:
Note: The Runa-side function signature must include the Objective-C ABI's
Note: implicit first two args (receiver and selector) as explicit Runa
Note: parameters. The user normally writes a wrapper that hides this.
Note:
Note: Expected output (Darwin):
Note:   - Compilation: exit 0
Note:   - Assembly: callq _objc_msgSend@PLT at the doSomething call site
Note:   - Link: against libobjc.dylib (implicit add_library "objc")
Note:
Note: Expected output (non-Darwin):
Note:   - Compilation: exit 0 (compiler doesn't validate target until link)
Note:   - Link: HARD ERROR with diagnostic about objc requiring Darwin

External Process called "doSomething"
    that takes self_obj as Integer, selector as Integer, arg as Integer
    returns Integer
    from library "objc"
    convention objc

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: Use opaque integers for receiver and selector — in real Objective-C
    Note: interop, the user resolves these via runtime helpers (objc_getClass,
    Note: sel_registerName). This file's purpose is purely to verify the
    Note: codegen and link emission paths.
    Let self_handle be 0
    Let selector be 0
    Let arg_value be 42

    Let result be doSomething(self_handle, selector, arg_value)
    Return result
End Process
